Q: What is CSS?
Cascading stylesheet.
Is responsible for the styling of the document (DOM)

Q: Is the CSS static?
Yes, but you can use jquery to identify elements and .addClass
$('.post').addClass('highlight')

Q: How many ways can U call my stylesheet?
1. embedded stylesheet (in head section of the html file)
    <style type="text/css">
      body {
        padding-top: 60px;   
        padding-bottom: 40px;
      }   
    </style>
2. inline style (in html element section with style attribute )
<body style="background-color: red">
3. with an external stylesheet
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="css/bootstrap.min.css">
4. Scoped style
<div>
    <style type="text/css" scoped>
        h1 {color: #C03}
        p {color: #0C6}
    </style>
    <h1>Welcome to this page</h1>
    <p>This is all I have to say about this page.</p>
</div>
5.
With an import directive in an already included stylesheet

Q: With so many class and subclass, how to find properties that apply to my element?
Chromium
> developer tools
> Element
Look at the CSS

Q: With so many colors and numbers, how can I find the right color set?
http://kuler.adobe.com/#create/fromacolor
You can start from a color or from an imported image
